  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6592.11 sitting directly between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-36.4B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+24.4B), dealers are currently forced to buy this minor dip as they're short gamma in breakout regime. The massive negative gamma cluster from 6575-6590 creates a dangerous amplification zone where any selling pressure will force dealers to sell more, while the positive gamma wall at 6605 acts as the key resistance where dealers will aggressively sell rallies. Watch for a potential violent move if we break below 6590 toward the 6580/6585 negative walls, or a reversal bounce if we can reclaim 6605.\n\n**Bottom line:** Expect sharp moves in either direction with current spot trapped between major opposing gamma forces.",
